From c6a7fa740a1325bea4cd385d2999dfe6e4e6289a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rameshkumar Sundaram <ramess@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 9 Aug 2025 01:15:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:CP: wifi: mac80211: assign vlan chanctx for
 non-ML vlan interfaces

While assigning channel context for a master AP interface the same context
should be copied to all the associated AP VLAN interfaces. However, for
Non-ML AP VLAN interfaces this is not happening as vif->valid_links
is checked against the AP VLAN link id on which the context is copied.

For non-ML AP VLANs, vif->valid_links will not be set but
vif->link_conf[0] will always hold the reference of vif->bss_conf and
its default link id will be set to 0.

As a result, TX packets from AP VLAN interfaces are getting dropped
with below warning as they are scheduled for transmission without an
active channel.

WARNING: CPU: 0 PID: 8 at net/mac80211/tx.c:6542 ieee80211_tx_skb_tid+0xbc/0x17e [mac80211]
Call Trace:
 ieee80211_tx_skb_tid+0x3d/0x17e [mac80211]
 ieee80211_tx_skb_tid+0xbc/0x17e [mac80211]
 __ieee80211_start_rx_ba_session+0x793/0xc34 [mac80211]
 sta_info_get_bss+0xa7/0xb4 [mac80211]
 ieee80211_process_addba_request+0x91/0x9e [mac80211]
 ieee80211_iface_work+0x194/0x5a6 [mac80211]
 process_one_work+0x211/0x477
 cfg80211_wiphy_work+0xb7/0xe4 [cfg80211]

Check valid_links only for ML AP VLAN interfaces to allow copying master
AP's context to both ML and non-ML AP VLAN interfaces properly.

Patch-Dependency: 0141-wifi-mac80211-Changes-for-WDS-MLD.patch
Patch-work: None

Fixes: I2a6f3d80a30 ("cfg80211/mac80211: Validate link to use link conf")
Signed-off-by: Rameshkumar Sundaram <ramess@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/chan.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/chan.c b/net/mac80211/chan.c
index b32b544ecfa1..dfee441f292b 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/chan.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/chan.c
@@ -1095,7 +1095,7 @@ __ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans(struct ieee80211_link_data *link,
 	list_for_each_entry(vlan, &sdata->u.ap.vlans, u.vlan.list) {
 		struct ieee80211_bss_conf *vlan_conf;
 
-		if (!(vlan->vif.valid_links & BIT(link_id)))
+		if (vlan->vif.valid_links && !(vlan->vif.valid_links & BIT(link_id)))
 			continue;
 
 		vlan_conf = wiphy_dereference(local->hw.wiphy,
@@ -1344,7 +1344,7 @@ ieee80211_link_update_chanreq(struct ieee80211_link_data *link,
 	list_for_each_entry(vlan, &sdata->u.ap.vlans, u.vlan.list) {
 		struct ieee80211_bss_conf *vlan_conf;
 
-		if (!(vlan->vif.valid_links & BIT(link_id)))
+		if (vlan->vif.valid_links && !(vlan->vif.valid_links & BIT(link_id)))
 			continue;
 
 		vlan_conf = wiphy_dereference(sdata->local->hw.wiphy,
-- 
